.TH setIoRowMargin  22.14 "Fri Oct 06 02:12:27 2023" 
.SH Name \fBsetIoRowMargin\fR \-  Sets the distance from the die boundary edge to the I/O row starting edge location
.SH Syntax \fBsetIoRowMargin\fR  [-help]  side   row   margin 
.P Sets the distance from the die boundary edge to the I/O row starting edge location. You can use this command for multiple I/O rows.
.P Note: You can use the Edit I/O Ring form to specify I/O pad rings and row margins for multiple rows. Alternatively, to achieve the same using text commands, you must first use the setIoRowMargin command to set the distance from the die boundary edge to start of each row and then use the placePadIO command to place the I/O pads evenly between these rows. 
.SH Parameters   "\fB-help\fR" Outputs a brief description that includes the type and default information for each setIoRowMargin parameter. For a detailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use the man command:  man setIoRowMargin  "\fB<side>\fR" Specifies the side of the I/O row margin, where n is the North side, w is the West side, s is the South side, and e is the East side.  Data_type: string, optional  "\fB<margin>\fR" Specifies the distance between the die boundary edge to the I/O row edge, in microns.  Data_type: float, optional  "\fB<row>\fR" Specifies the I/O row number. This value can be up to 8 rows. You can also use this value in conjunction with the placePadIO and placePIO -optIOs commands to specify the number of rows for placing peripheral I/O cells for the CLASS PAD and CLASS PAD AREAIO flows respectively.
.RS  "*" 2 To create and optimize multiple I/O Rows in a CLASS PAD flow, use the following commands:   setIoRowMargin row  placePadIO  "*" 2 To create and optimize multiple I/O Rows in a CLASS PAD AREAIO flow, use the following commands:   setIoRowMargin rowNumber  placePIO -optIOs
.RE   Maximum: 1000  Minimum: 0  Data_type: int, optional 
.SH Example
.P The following command sets the North side of the second I/O row starting edge value at 300 microns from the die boundary edge to the second I/O row edge:  setIoRowMargin n 2 300 
.SH Related Information
.RS  "*" 2 placePadIO  "*" 2 placePIO  "*" 2 Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide  "*" 2 Floorplan Menu chapter in the Innovus Menu Reference
.RS  "*" 2 Edit I/O Ring
.RE 
.RE
.P
